### ğŸ§  Summary

| Function Family         | Type Safety | Reason                                                   |
| ----------------------- | ----------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `printf()`, `scanf()`   | âŒ No        | Variadic arguments (`...`) â†’ compiler canâ€™t verify types |
| `std::cout`, `std::cin` | âœ… Yes       | Overloaded operators â†’ compiler checks types             |

---

### ğŸ§  In short:

> `printf()` and `scanf()` are *not type-safe* because the **format string** and **actual arguments** are not verified by the compiler.

